 What is Shell Scripting?
Shell scripting is the process of writing commands in a file and executing them automatically.

Why DevOps Engineers Use Shell Scripts:
Server Automation
Deployment Automation
Monitoring
Backup Operations
Log Analysis

First Script:
#!/bin/bash

echo "Hello DevOps Engineer"

Execute:

chmod +x script.sh
./script.sh

Variables:
#!/bin/bash

NAME="Arul"

echo "Welcome $NAME"

User Input:
#!/bin/bash

read -p "Enter your Name: " NAME

echo "Hello $NAME"

Conditions:
#!/bin/bash

AGE=18

if [ $AGE -ge 18 ]
then
    echo "Eligible"
else
    echo "Not Eligible"
fi

Loops:
#!/bin/bash

for i in {1..5}
do
    echo $i
done

Real-Time Example:
Check Disk Usage
#!/bin/bash

df -h
